  "instructions": [
    "preheat the oven to 400f.",
    "toast the peanuts in a 350f oven for 5-7 minutes or until fragrant.",
    "heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "saute the onion and garlic until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the cumin, coriander, garam masala, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper. stir to combine.",
    "add the toasted peanuts, dashi powder, and 2 cups of water to the skillet. stir to combine.",
    "bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 10-12 minutes or until the liquid has reduced and the peanuts are coated in the spice blend.",
    "transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish and roast in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes or until the top is golden brown and the peanuts are caramelized.",
    "garnish with chopped fresh parsley and serve hot."
  ],
